This issue should be addressed to the Government, Knesset, Cabinet in general and to all the politicians. Unfortunately, the public does not become aware of the breakdowns and cracks in the system and because there is no demand for change, there is extravagance and mostly.Cynically said; the politicians would not change anything because after the voter registers a complaint, he will vote for the same electoral ticket because he prefers the other candidate to the one he knew before.

The transfer of information is a two way street—On the one hand Tkadsat and CTS call the politicians, especially on Shabat and help them to avoid sins by calling them on the Sabbath, and on the other hand, when there is a " BIG HAPPENING" politicians call CTS and ask them to help them with describing the big event in a way that will pay dividends in public relations. Sometimes, though on a low level policies, which will make the people feel that they are doing something towards good publicity and not being a victim of greed. The politicians know that ultimately they would be voted out of their jobs in a unique style. To a true believer in "Truth-In-Reporting" this should explain the process to the reader.
